(109, 'torts', '18. Defense of Infancy, Insanity or Incompetence?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-24 23:06:35', 1),
(110, 'torts', '19. Negligence?', '<p>Under tort law <b>NEGLIGENCE</b> is a <b>failure to exercise</b> that degree of care that a reasonably prudent person would use in the same situation. To prevail the plaintiff must usually prove <b>DUTY</b>, <b>BREACH</b>, <b>ACTUAL</b> and <b>PROXIMATE</b> CAUSATION and <b>DAMAGES</b>.</p><p>If the question is <b>only of negligence</b> then add following:</p><p>If B can prove the elements of a prima facie case of negligence A may be liable.&nbsp;Then analyze duty, breach, etc. each as a separate issue.</p><p><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-28 01:37:33', 1),
